title: Import & Processing
text: spiro package makes import processing cardiopulmonary data easy: spiro() function work . just need paste path file raw data cardiopulmonary exercise testing function. return data.frame containing relevant data second testing, ready summarizing plotting. spiro() return interpolated data following parameters: load: velocity power, either retrieved raw data file manually supplied setting protocol step: coded variable number load step test protocol time: time (s) VO2: oxygen uptake (ml/min) VCO2: carbon dioxide output (ml/min) RR: respiratory rate (1/min) VT: tidal volume (l) VE: minute ventilation (l/min) HR: heart rate (bpm), available PetO2: end-tidal partial pressure oxygen (mmHg) PetCO2: end-tidal partial pressure carbon dioxide (mmHg) VO2_rel: relative oxygen uptake (ml/min/kg) VCO2_rel: relative carbon dioxide output (ml/min/kg) RE: running economy (ml/kg/km), applicable RER: respiratory quotient CHO: rate carbohydrate oxidation (g/min) FO: rate fat oxidation (g/min)

title: Import & Processing
text: highly recommended import raw breath--breath data several reasons: Prior averaging interpolation happens outside R therefore non-reproducible data processing step. data single breaths available, functionality package lost (e.g. breath-based averaging VO_2max_ determination). Prior processing usually leads data containing less data points, hinders automated guessing exercise protocols based available load data. use metabolic cart measures, output data breath--breath basis, read manufacturer’s instructions export raw data way. Data systems (e.g., mixing chamber metabolic carts) can still processed spiro-package, protocol guesses summary calculations treated caution.

title: Import & Processing

title: Summarizing & Plotting
Summarizing & Plotting
text: analysis gas exchange data, often mean parameters performed load step interest. ensure presence metabolic steady state, end step used calculations. length computational interval (seconds) can modified interval argument. interval exceeds length step, shortened steps displaying note. can turn messages setting argument quiet = TRUE.

title: Summarizing & Plotting
text: types exercise tests may preferable get maximal values measured parameters (e.g., maximum oxygen uptake VO2max). spiro_max() calculates smoothing data. smooth argument controls interval method data smoothing. Different smoothing methods available: Moving averages fixed time intervals (e.g. smooth = 30 30 seconds), moving averages fixed number breaths (e.g. smooth = "30b" 30 breaths) digital filters (e.g. smooth = "0.04fz3" third-order zero-phase low-pass Butterworth filter cut-frequency 0.04 Hz). Per default smoothing apply heart rate values, can enable behavior hr_smooth = TRUE.
code: spiro_max(gxt_data, smooth = 30) #>       VO2    VCO2     VE VO2_rel  RER HR #> 1 4732.28 4640.75 129.62    71.7 0.99 NA

title: Summarizing & Plotting
text: spiro package lets visualize data cardiopulmonary exercise testing: spiro_plot() can display traditional Wasserman 9-Panel Plot.  can individually select combine panels 9-Panel Plot setting argument.  Data time (Panel 1,2,3,6,8,9) displayed smoothed, determined via smooth argument. panels (4,5,7) use raw breath--breath data visualization. can control appearance plots spiro_plot(). Use base_size argument change plot base size. Pass style arguments ggplot::theme() customization.
code: # load example data data <- spiro(spiro_example("zan_ramp"), hr_file = spiro_example("hr_ramp.tcx"))  spiro_plot(data) # Plot only V-Slope (Panel 5) and VO2/VCO2 over time (Panel 3) spiro_plot(data, which = c(5,3)) # Change base size and axis label font spiro_plot(   data,    base_size = 9,    axis.title = ggplot2::element_text(face = "italic", colour = "blue") )

title: Return maximum values from cardiopulmonary exercise tests — spiro_max
text: calculating maximum values, raw data smoothed. Default smoothing method 30-second rolling average. See smooth argument spiro_smooth options, breath-based averages digital filtering. Parameters calculated maximum oxygen uptake (absolute relative), carbon dioxide output, minute ventilation, respiratory exchange ratio (RER), heart rate. maximum value defined highest single data values smoothing. maximum RER different algorithm used, RER rest may exceed peak value exercise. Therefore values last ten percent exercise time considered RERmax determination. RERmax calculation works best data tests without rest intervals (e.g., ramp tests) attached load protocol data.

text: data frame

title: Apply a smoothing filter to data from cardiopulmonary exercise testing. — spiro_smooth
text: Raw data cardiopulmonary usually noisy due measurement errors biological breath--breath variability. processing visualizing gas exchange data, often helpful filter raw data. function provides different filtering methods (time average, breath average, digital filters). Breath-based digital filters applied raw breath--breath data. Time-based averages conducted interpolated data.

title: Apply a smoothing filter to data from cardiopulmonary exercise testing. — spiro_smooth
text: Time-Based Average (e.g. smooth = 30) (centered) moving average defined timespan. number can given integer character (e.g. smooth = "30") defines length calculation interval seconds. Breath-Based Average (e.g. smooth = "15b") (centered) moving average defined number breaths. integer letter 'b' defines number breaths calculation interval. Butterworth filter (e.g. smooth = "0.04f3") digital Butterworth filter (lag). number letter 'f' defines low-pass cut-frequency, number gives order filter. See bw_filter details. Zero-lag Butterworth filter (e.g. smooth = "0.04fz3") digital forwards-backwards Butterworth filter (without lag). number letter 'f' defines low-pass cut-frequency, number gives order filter. See bw_filter details.
